a.text: The peonies were the first casualty
They tore this chair apart. Vandals.
This poor vase was used as a weapon.
How'd they reach the chandelier? It's ruined!
Remember the lounge walls you fixed? Well...
Roddy was thrown onto the slot machines.
The speaker is barely holding on.
Decor knocked off. This place is falling apart.
Charlie's favorite table now has scratches all over.
They reduced a statue to rubble. Truly disgraceful.
More flowers ruined. I can't bear it.
They flipped over the chairs. Why do this?
The couch reeks of spilled drinks. A complete disaster.
This table has an Arthur shaped hole.
More picture frames all over. Terrifying.
They threw picture frames at each other. Disgusting.
They broke another vase. Of course they did.
Cushions, torn apart. No respect at all.
They overturned tables outside. Was this truly necessary?
They knocked the lamp post over. Spectacular work.
Fence plank loosened. Another fine touch.
This bench toppled over while they tussled.
Roddy's head bent the gate quite a bit.
This broken vase was 100 years old.
Another ruined decoration. My heart can't take this.
More of my poor flowers ruined.
The fight reached its climax outside, at the garden.
They splashed mud all over like beasts.
They chipped the fountain edge with their heads.
Pebbles all over. Because why not.
The last mess to fix. Finally.
